// Keraunios PvE Season 28 Lawless
//notes: (PvE / M+KB): [Tier: S] [MW: Handling] 
(PvE Roll: All-Around), 
(Fluted Barrel), (Light Battery), 
[Shoot to Loot] (also good: Supercharged Magazine) 
[Chain Reaction] (also good: Rolling Storm or Jolting Feedback) Masterwork Handling)
To improve the feel of Keraunios, we recommend Fluted Barrel, Light Battery, and a Handling Masterwork, boosting the Handling to 84.
In the first perk slot, Shoot to Loot is an excellent utility option as it allows the Trace Rifle user (who is typically a Cenotaph supporting Warlock) to safely secure Special and Heavy ammo from range.
Alternatively, if you’d like to lean more into Arc, Supercharged Magazine is a great option. 
In perk slot 2, we suggest Chain Reaction as it improves the add-clearing capabilities of the weapon by adding some AoE damage, something that Trace Rifles notoriously struggle with.
However, if you leaned into Arc with Supercharged Magazine, it may make sense to stick with that trend and go for Rolling Storm or Jolting Feedback instead if you want a more subclass-synergistic option.|tags:pve,mkb
