// The Heron
//notes: (PvE / M+KB): [Tier: S], [MW: Shield Duration], [Nail, Meet Hammer]
PvE Roll: All-Around
Haft 	[Auxiliary Reserves]
Magazine 	[Alloy Magazine]
Perk 1 	[Repulsor Brace] (also good: Lead from Gold)
Perk 2 	[Destabilizing Rounds] (also good: Sword Logic)
Since the main draw of glaives is their ridiculous damage resistance, it’s best to boost the uptime of the shield as much as possible, 
so we’ll go with Auxiliary Reserves and a Shield Duration masterwork to aid in that. 
Alloy Mag is going to greatly help with reload speed here given the low mag size.
For Perk 1, Repulsor Brace is your best choice, bar none. The shield from the glaive already provides 97.5% damage resistance, 
but that’s only while active, so what better way to keep you in the fight than by getting a second source of DR? 
And how will you keep Repulsor Brace active? 
Through our Perk 2 choice, Destabilizing Rounds. 
These two are a welcome sight on any weapon, and now that it’s finally on a glaive, 
you can really lean into that CQC fantasy without needing to fully commit to a melee build.
|tags:pve,mkb
