// Mistral Lift PvE god rolls
//notes: (PvE / M+KB): [Tier: S], [MW: Charge Time], [Origin: Veist Stinger]
PvE Roll: All-Around
Barrel 	[Fluted Barrel]
Battery [Liquid Coils] or [Accelerated Coils]
Perk 1 	[Envious Arsenal] (also good: Reconstruction)
Perk 2 	[Bait and Switch] (also good: Precision Instrument)
On Mistral Lift, we first take Fluted Barrel as it boosts the Handling and Stability of the weapon, making it easier to use. 
For the magazine, you can go with either Liquid Coils or Accelerated Coils. The latter will do slightly more damage per second, 
but Liquid Coils will be more damage overall, however, the actual damage difference between both options is very low. Charge Time is the best masterwork available.
For perks, we suggest Envious Arsenal in the first column as it is an excellent reload perk, however, Reconstruction is an okay backup. 
Bait and Switch is the go-to for perk 2 as it is the best damage perk available on Mistral Lift, but Precision Instrument is a reasonable backup option.|tags:pve,mkb
